Text: President Trump’s decision to withdraw from the Iran Nuclear Deal dangerously damages our country’s credibility and undermines the safety & security of the American people.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: The Iran deal has serious flaws, but it would be better to have this deal in place and address other issues outside of the deal, because without it, the alternative is a war against Iran to prevent them from developing a nuclear weapon.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: So Trump has increased likelihood of war with Iran & has undermined the critical negotiations to denuclearize North Korea - a country that already has nuclear weapons that threaten the people of Hawaii and this country.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Trump's message to Iran, NK, & world: It's ok to sign an agreement, then rip it up down the road. Kim Jong-un will say: "Why should I trust the U.S. to adhere to an agreement with North Korea when you did not adhere to the agreement with Iran, even though Iran was in compliance?"
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Trump proudly said: "When I make promises, I keep them." But what about the US, who he supposedly represents? The United States made a promise in that agreement with Iran, UK, France, Germany, Russia, and China. Trump has now broken that promise, undermining U.S. credibility.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Why should any ally or adversary believe anything the US says? Why should they trust we will keep our word? Trump has completely undermined the opportunity to prevent conflicts & war through negotiation and agreement, by ripping up the agreement the US made with Iran & allies
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text:

  https://t.co/9tDPQriojD

Text: I'm going into this weekend resolved and committed to tackling the opioid crisis. I flew home to Hawaiʻi after introducing the Opioid Crisis Accountability Act, the companion bill to @BernieSanders' opioid bill. It’s time to end the opioid crisis—here’s how we’re going to do it:
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: We can create the momentum needed to bring this tragic, expensive, and deadly opioid crisis to a halt, but we need everyone's support. Call, text, tweet—do whatever it takes to get the word out. Big Pharma is going to come at us with everything they’ve got—we need to fight back.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Have drug companies reimburse the cost of the crisis—$78 billion a year, according to the CDC. Multi-billion dollar profits from a prescription drug trade that results in death and human suffering should be appropriated to solve the crisis they helped create.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Hold top company executives criminally liable for the crisis. This isn’t about escalating the so-called “War on Drugs.” It’s about restoring justice to a criminal justice system that has been out of whack punishing the wrong people for generations.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Prohibit and penalize the false marketing and distribution of opioids. Companies like Purdue Pharma, the makers of OxyContin, knew about the dangerous and addictive nature of their drugs but did nothing to inform doctors, pharmacists, or the public.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: I love you Mom! #happymothersday https://t.co/JI6DT429yx
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Pharmaceutical companies have lied, cheated, and swindled the American people by pushing dangerously addictive opioids onto the public with no regard for the death, addiction, and despair they have caused. We are demanding real change - Big Pharma must be held accountable.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: The Senate vote to keep #NetNeutrality rules in place and overturn the FCC decision is a victory for everyone who believes in a fair, open, and equal Internet for all.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Now the House needs to pass legislation to overturn FCC repeal of #NetNeutrality - call your representative and urge them to support the preservation of equal and open access to the Internet.

Text: As we mourn the victims of today’s devastating shooting at #SantaFeHighSchool, my heart is with their families and the whole community. Our children should not have to live in fear for their lives when they go to school. We MUST come together & do all we can to keep our kids safe
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Over 70 organizations like @cut_50 support the #FIRSTSTEPAct as they work to reduce our nation's prison population of 2.3M people. This bipartisan bill is an important first step to achieving comprehensive criminal justice & sentencing reform #prisonreform https://t.co/5PE2wEGXxK
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: We can no longer afford to maintain the conditions of a broken system. We spend more than $80 billion a year locking up 2.3 million people—more than any country on earth. I support the #FIRSTSTEPAct and ask you to stand with me for real positive change.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: The #FIRSTSTEPAct is an opportunity to make meaningful, positive policy changes on #prisonreform that work for the people of Hawaiʻi and the country at-large.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: We still need sentencing reform, but we can’t take an all-or-nothing approach on #prisonreform. We need to focus on the changes we can make today, and the #FIRSTSTEPAct is one of those changes.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: In hyper-partisan Washington, passing bipartisan legislation is rare. But one thing that has brought Ds and Rs together is the need to fix our criminal justice system. Tomorrow we can begin to do that by passing the #FIRSTSTEPAct in the House. #prisonreform
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: According to the National Institute of Justice, three out of every four people who spend time in prison will be rearrested within five years. The #FIRSTSTEPAct can begin to change this. #prisonreform
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Too many people get stuck in our broken criminal justice system and never make it out. We can’t take an all or nothing approach to reform while so many people and families suffer under the status quo. The #FIRSTSTEPAct is the first step towards comprehensive #prisonreform.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: One piece of legislation won’t fix every problem in our #criminaljustice system. The #FIRSTSTEPAct is the common ground that exists today where we can get something good done now that will have a direct effect on people’s lives, while we continue to work toward #prisonreform.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Formerly incarcerated people face huge legal obstacles to finding employment and housing after release. Rejoining society is often too difficult, leading to many ending up back behind bars. This leaves broken families in its wake. We need #prisonreform now.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: The #FIRSTSTEPAct uses evidence-based approaches that have already been proven to help states like Texas, Alabama and Alaska reduce crime, keep families together, and shrink prison populations, reducing cost to taxpayers.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: The #FIRSTSTEPAct makes sure that prisoners are treated, assessed, and rehabilitated with policies that are based on evidence, not personal or institutional bias.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Prisons are overcrowded, and they’re costing Americans big time -- America pays more than $80 billion a year to be exact. #FIRSTSTEPAct ensures pre-release halfway houses or home confinement is available and gives people tools to reenter society & end cycle of recidivism.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Real change requires people coming together and taking action. #FIRSTSTEPAct will come before Congress tomorrow, with bipartisan support. But some are putting politics before the well-being of people, and opposing this. Urge Congress to vote YES for #prisonreform tomorrow.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: According to the National Institute of Justice, three out of every four people who spend time in prison will be rearrested for a new crime within five years. The #FIRSTSTEPAct is our opportunity to make real, bipartisan progress on reforming the criminal justice system right now. https://t.co/u0NtdpRHNB
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text:

✔️ House of Reps

SIGN ON + let's ensure it gets signed into law: https://t.co/NjMRTVC2Dk https://t.co/ocg9wVRQqx
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Last night I proudly cast my vote for the bipartisan #FirstStepAct which will begin long-overdue #PrisonReform. This will make a real difference in people's lives, now & in the future. Thanks to my friends @RepJeffries @RepDougCollins @VanJones68 & @cut_50 for their leadership!
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Next step for the the #FirstStepAct is to get the Senate to pass this bill with similar overwhelming bipartisan support as we saw in the House last night.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: In just a couple hours there will be a vote on the House floor on my amendment to strip the #NDAA of a provision that authorizes our military to go to war with Iran, without limits, and without any constitutionally required declaration of war by Congress or debate.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: My amendment upholds Congress’s constitutional responsibility to declare war, and stops this #NDAA provision that sidelines the American people and cedes congressional authority to warhawks like John Bolton, Mike Pompeo, and Nikki Haley
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Authorizing Section 1225 gives the Trump Administration total authority to keep deploying our troops to the Middle East as long as they want to, without any clear objective and without congressional authorization. This puts us on a dangerous path to endless war.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: #Ndaa Section 1225 gives after-the-fact license to continuing U.S. military actions in Yemen supporting Saudi Arabia which have resulted in mass starvation, tens of thousands of dead civilians, and blockades causing one of the worst humanitarian disasters in history.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Im urging my colleagues to vote YES on the Gabbard amendment that will be up for a vote today in the House which will simply strip Section 1225 from the #NDAA - upholding our constitutional responsibility and preventing this blank check for endless war from becoming law.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Rather than dumping trillions more dollars into more interventionist regime change wars, we should be using our precious resources to invest in our communities here at home - providing clean water, rebuilding infrastructure, improving education, housing, healthcare & more
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Without a clear objective, you end up in endless war. So what is the objective of #NDAA Section 1225 authorizing war to ‘counter Iran’? Is it regime change in Iran? Regime change in Syria? More war in Syria? Yemen?
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: For too long, the U.S. has engaged in military adventurism and interventionist wars, sending our troops overseas, with no clear objective or end state. ‘Countering Iran’ is not an end state that our military or diplomats can achieve.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: I strongly urge Congress to consider the serious consequences of Section 1225 which would authorize any or all of these actions. Congress must not cede its authority to declare war to the Administration. I urge my colleagues to vote YES on my amendment to strip Sec1225 from #NDAA
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: The seriousness of North Korea's nuclear threat to the American people cannot be overstated. The need for direct talks between Trump and Kim is critical and urgent to peacefully negotiate denuclearization of #NorthKorea, remove nuclear threat, and avoid all-out catastrophic war.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: We must be willing to meet with adversaries or leaders of nations who aren't our allies to further the cause of peace. I strongly urge @realDonaldTrump to engage in direct talks with #NorthKorea's Kim Jong Un without preconditions. The stakes are high & there is no time to waste.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: While many Americans may relate to growing up in a conservative home, my story is a little different because my father was very outspoken. He was an activist who was fighting against gay rights and marriage equality in Hawaii – and at that time, I forcefully defended him.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: But I also grew up in a socially conservative household, where I was raised to believe that marriage should only be between a man and a woman. For a period of my life I didn’t see the contradiction in those beliefs.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: I grew up knowing that every person is a child of God, and equally loved by God. I have always believed in the fundamental rights and equality of all people.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: That cannot happen, because every single American deserves to be treated equally – by their fellow Americans and under the law. I will continue to fight for LGBTQ+ people, whether they’re in school or serving in uniform, trying to get healthcare, or taking care of their family.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: I know that LGBTQ+ people still struggle, are still facing discrimination, are still facing abuse and still fear that their hard-won rights are going to be taken away by people who hold views like I used to.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: My views have changed significantly since then, and my record in Congress over the last 6 years reflects what is in my heart: A strong and ongoing commitment to fighting for LGBTQ+ rights.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: Many years ago, I apologized for my words and, more importantly, for the negative impact that they had. I sincerely repeat my apology today.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: I regret the role I played in causing such pain, and I remain committed to fighting for LGBTQ+ equality. You can learn more about my legislative record here: https://t.co/EDmF7KuMvY
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: I’m so grateful to my friends and loved ones, both gay and straight, who patiently helped me see how my past positions on these issues were at odds with my values, my aloha, and that they were causing people harm.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: When we divide people based on who they are or who they love, all we are doing is adding fuel to the flames that perpetuate bigotry and hatred.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: When we deny LGBTQ+ people the basic rights that exist for every American, we are denying their humanity - denying that they are equal. We are also creating a dangerous environment that breeds discrimination and violence.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: I look forward to being able to share more of my story and experiences growing up – not as an excuse, but in the hopes that it may inspire others to truly live aloha; to love and care for others.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard

Text: But over the years, I formed my own opinions based on my life experience that changed my views – at a personal level in having aloha, love, for all people, and ensuring that every American, regardless of sexual orientation or gender identity, is treated equally under the law.
Name: Tulsi Gabbard
